cs.SI, cs.CL, cs.MM, cs.CY, cs.HC 

This paper deals with the analysis of user-generated content on two popular social media platforms, Twitter and Instagram. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). The paper also involves textual and visual analysis, which falls under cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.MM (Multimedia). The study also explores the differences in user perception of the two platforms, which could be related to cs.CY (Computers and Society) and cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction).
